                <img id="Johnson" src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FMEXFfrVEAENYdi?format=jpg&name=large"/>
                <p id="Johnson-caption" style="opacity: 0.0; transition: 0.1s ease-in-out">   Katherine Johnson is an African American mathematician. She worked for NASA during the space race in opposition to the Soviet Union. She and her colleagues were often known as “human computers” due to their expertise in mathematics. The calculations she made were critical to putting people in the United States of America in orbit. This great accomplishment was a majority of the reason how humans were able to travel to the moon. </p>

