            <div class = "minority-in-stem"> 
                <div class = "minority-subtitle"> minority women in stem:</div>
                <img src = "https://www.relocatemagazine.com/media/images/iStock-1060970374_17202_t12.jpg" class = "minoritycenter">
                <br> Many people of color are underrepresented in STEM fields. This is especially true for people of Hispanic, African American, or Native American backgrounds. Women of color experience the intersection of discrimination based on their gender and race and are underrepresented compared to white men and women in STEM fields. “Many organizations have dedicated themselves toward promoting and advancing STEM education for girls including Girl Start, Girls WhoCode, and the National Girls Collaborative Project”.
                <br> People in STEM with disabilities are in the labor force, according to data from the NSF. However, the people with disabilities in the workforce make up roughly seventeen more percent than those who do not. Ultimately, having a disability makes it harder to retain employment in STEM.
                <br> Students with disabilities can face unique challenges in college, giving them an unequal disadvantage. Given the harsh environments that women in STEM majors already face, it’s important to make sure that women with disabilities are given all of the tools they need to reach success.
                <br> As veteran members are part of the armed forces, they are afforded opportunities to learn technical skills that are marketable and easily are able to be translated into college credits.They should be given more opportunities since a majority of them still decide to pursue other professions or desire to further their STEM education.
                <br> LGBTQ+ individuals often face discrimination and harsh environments in STEM fields. “However, while retention rates for gay men in STEM majors are lower than those of straight men, gay women were actually retained at a higher rate than straight women.” Women part of this minority group still face great discrimination, and their retention rates are below those for straight white men. STEM departments should provide resources for LGBTQ students to contribute to them feeling safe, protected, and respected in addition to their college education.
            </div>
